cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is about relation classification, which is a task in natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a new loss function for the convolutional neural network, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the use of word embeddings as input features is a common technique in NLP and falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves text classification, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the use of neural networks for classification is a common technique in the category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
